Time Complexity:

Let n = size of array

    Nested loops → O(n²)

Overall: O(n²)


Space Complexity:

    No extra space used

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Initialize maxDis = minimum value

2. Traverse array using two loops:

   - Outer loop (i from 0 to n-2)
   - Inner loop (j from i+1 to n-1)

3. For each pair (i, j):
   - If colors[i] != colors[j]:
     → Update maxDis = max(maxDis, j - i)

4. After checking all pairs:
   - Return maxDis





class Solution {
    public int maxDistance(int[] colors) {
        int maxDis = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i=0; i<colors.length-1; i++){
            for(int j=i+1; j<colors.length; j++){
                if(colors[i]!=colors[j]) maxDis = Math.max(maxDis, j-i);
            }
        }
        return maxDis;
    }
}
